OL,3,CMan 'pointed out homes of migrant
OL,4,Cneighbours' for attacks, court told
OL,6,FDefence barrister Luke Curran argued
OL,7,Fthat Watson had only tried to ensure
OL,8,Fno damage was done to his own home.
OL,10,F"He is on very good terms with his
OL,11,Fneighbours... and indicates that he
OL,12,Fhas been involved in cross-community
OL,13,Fwork locally," Mr Curran added.
OL,15,FDenying bail to Watson, Mr Justice
OL,16,FFowler highlighted the incitement to
OL,17,Fhatred charge he faces.
OL,19,FThe judge held: "I am concerned there
OL,20,Fis a risk of further offences in this
OL,21,Fcase."
